member.remarks:
Must refer to a static function accepting a single parameter of the "entity" type. 
            For example: 

              public static string GetFullName(IPerson person) { 
                return person.FirstName + " " + person.LastName; 
              }

            c# does not allow specifying method references as attribute parameters. As a workaround, we 
            denote method using (Type, Method name) pair.

You can provide a Format string with embedded property names enclosed in braces, for ex: "{Title}"). Alternatively you can use a custom formatting method - in this case you must provide the name and container class and method name pointing to a static method with signature like
public static string DisplayBook(IBook book)' {..}
Examples: [Display("{Title}")] [Display("{LastName}, {FirstName}")] [Display(typeof(BookExtensions), "DisplayBook")]
